NAME
	dbbackup -- back up a MySQL database in a Rails environment.

SYNOPSIS
	dbbackup <environment> [/full/path/to/mysqldump] [--no-gzip] [--no-svn]

DESCRIPTION
    By default, dbbackup gets the DB info from config/database.yml, dumps and gzips it into "<Rails Root>/db/dump_<environment>.sql.gz",
	and	adds/commits that to Subversion.
	
	
	The following parameters are available:
	<environment> 			Required, must be defined in config/database.yml
	/path/to/mysqldump		If mysqldump isn't in PATH or has a different name than "mysqldump" (eg, some OS X installs use "mysqldump5")
	--no-gzip				Don't gzip the output file
	--no-commit				Don't commit the output file to Subversion			
	
EXAMPLES
	dbbackup production		Creates 'db/dump_production.sql.gz' and commits it to Subversion.

	dbbackup development /usr/local/mysql/bin/mysqldump --no-gzip --no-svn
							Creates 'db/dump_development.sql'